import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='time', y='count', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the overall trend of Github activity over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day_of_week'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day_of_week'], format='%A').dt.day_name()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='day_of_week', y='count', data=data, ci=None)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Github activity by day of the week?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['hour'] = pd.to_datetime(data['hour'], format='%H').dt.hour
    sns.barplot(x='hour', y='count', data=data, color='blue')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Github activity by hour of the day?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day_of_week'] = pd.Categorical(data['day_of_week'], categories=['Monday','Tuesday','Wednesday','Thursday','Friday','Saturday', 'Sunday'], ordered=True)
    chart = sns.scatterplot(x='day_of_week', y='count', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between Github activity and the day of the week?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
